Description: Online retailer of knives and multi-purpose tools
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Founding In early 2009, after being laid off from our respective jobs, my step-dad and I decided to venture into business together. Him, with over twenty years in the Recreational Vehicle industry and me with administrative and management experience, founded a mobile RV repair business. We decided to call the company J & S RV Service and Repair. We soon began marketing our new business online and in local publications. Within the first month we had a steady stream of clients, and that continued through the Summer of 2009. Need to Branch Out Around August we realized that most of our work will come between Spring and early Fall. At that point, I decided to expand the business and started advertising Recreational Vehicles on our company's website. Soon there was enough demand for our goods that a new company was established, branching off from our main company. The new company was called Miller Online Market. This, we believed would supplement the main part of the business during the colder months. As our success in product sales, again, continued to improve, we decided to dedicate more time to this part of the business. Much of our decision to focus more on the online part of the business was do to the decline in the mobile RV repair part of the business. End of Mobile Repair By early 2011, we decided to cease doing mobile repairs, and switch to the product sales full time. By then, in addition to selling RV products, we were also selling boating products and outdoor products.  At its height, Miller Online Market sold everything from Recreational Vehicle and boating products to outdoor and consumer electonics. In early 2013, the company's name changed again, this time to its current state -- Miller Knives, Inc. Currently Today, Miller Knives is an online retailer of knives, multi-purpose tools, and other related accessories. Our current website has been open since April 2014. Already, we have seen success in the short time we have been here. I am no longer in the RV business but I still have industry connections and access to RV parts. If you are interested in this, give me a call or send a message with "RV" as your subject.   If you ever have any questions or comments relating the business, itself, the products we sell, or any things else related the Miller Knives, we want to hear from you.

Description: Luminoto captures and preserves memories of the places you love the most.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Luminoto specializes in fine art photography of US cityscapes and landscapes taken by experienced photographers. Luminoto preserves memories and emotions of the places you love the most. Their experienced photographers devote years to exploring top US cities or journey to stunning landscapes enabling them to capture a diverse collection of unique fine art photography. Back in 1982, veteran photographer Bob Horsch opened up his first gallery in a small Chicago neighborhood. His business began to grow as locals visited the retial store to purchase fine art photographs as gifts or to decorate their homes and offices. To accomadate demand, the gallery was relocated to famous Michigan Avenue in 1991. It was open 7 days a week, 12 hours a day. After nearly 20 years in the retial business, the store closed in early 2008. Bob then took his business online with help from his son, Jeff, and created Horschgallery.com. Jeff was shocked that photographs were being sold to people all around the country. It was then that he wanted to help other talented cityscape and landscape photographers like his father sell more quality photos online. After years of throwing around ideas, he quit his job at age 31 to learn how to build the website he had envisioned. Eight months later, a new e-commerce photography business was born.

Full Description: Backyard Washer Toss is owned and operated by a father and son duo dedicated to providing the best washer toss products and best customer service online. Washer Toss has always been a part of our lives. While growing up, we always had an coffee can or pvc pipe dug into our backyard and we would play until there wasn't any light left in the day. We started Backyard Washer Toss because we weren't satisfied with quality or selection of the washer toss sets we found online. Most online stores sold only one or two styles of washer toss, and they weren't well made, or visually appealing. They all used the same kind of carpet, and they were all made of pine, which isn't durable. So we decided to build our own.   Our goal is to have our customers enjoy their washer toss sets for a long time, which is why we designed our sets to be durable. We also want our customers to have their own unique set. That's why we offer customized sets with 23 colors for both paint and carpet.

Description: The Center for Public Education provides clear, unbiased information about hot topics in public education.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: The Center for Public Education (Center) is a national resource for accurate, timely, and credible information about public education and its importance to the well-being of their nation. The Center provides up-to-date research, data, and analysis on current education issues and explores ways to improve student achievement and engage public support for public schools. Their intended audience includes school board members and other policymakers, educators, community leaders, parents, and everyone concerned with the education of their children. The Center is an initiative of the National School Boards Association (NSBA).
